black women have continued

00:40:55.840 --> 00:40:59.320
to be at the forefront
of this kind of activism

00:40:59.320 --> 00:41:05.000
for environmental justice,
food justice, clean water,

00:41:05.000 --> 00:41:12.080
safe communities, and just being
on the forefront of this EJ

00:41:12.080 --> 00:41:12.830
movement.

00:41:12.830 --> 00:41:15.770
And so I just wanted
to show that image,

00:41:15.770 --> 00:41:18.530
because I feel like it really
reflects how black women have

00:41:18.530 --> 00:41:20.412
continued in that tradition.

00:41:29.560 --> 00:41:35.260
To this question of
what gives me hope--

00:41:35.260 --> 00:41:38.740
I think what's
important for us to do

00:41:38.740 --> 00:41:42.400
is to be able to
tell our stories,

00:41:42.400 --> 00:41:45.010
and to listen to the voices
of people that really tend

00:41:45.010 --> 00:41:49.030
to be marginalized within this
whole discussion about what

00:41:49.030 --> 00:41:51.490
it means to have an
environmental movement

00:41:51.490 --> 00:41:52.930
in the US.

00:41:52.930 --> 00:41:58.270
And environmentalism, as
folks have been saying before,

00:41:58.270 --> 00:42:03.310
was sort of couched in this
saving our national parks,

00:42:03.310 --> 00:42:07.060
and the polar bears,
