where they're going to school,

00:42:13.060 --> 00:42:15.940
and making a lot of these
deeper intersections,

00:42:15.940 --> 00:42:18.880
and the impact of
environmental racism.

00:42:18.880 --> 00:42:21.130
And so I really believe
that it's important

00:42:21.130 --> 00:42:23.890
that we lift up the leadership
of people that are directly

00:42:23.890 --> 00:42:26.350
impacted by
environmental racism,

00:42:26.350 --> 00:42:29.380
environmental degradation.

00:42:29.380 --> 00:42:33.490
And that we start to put the
solutions and the resources

00:42:33.490 --> 00:42:38.285
in the hands of
those communities.

